AGENT AxiomLanguageTest
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 1
PURPOSE Validate that any Axiom file conforms to the AxiomLanguage meta-spec
GOAL Close the language loop — the Axiom language validates itself
     Every test case expressed in Axiom constructs only
     No external programming language syntax permitted

CANNOT_MUTATE test_definitions, pass_criteria, fail_criteria, meta_spec_reference

CONSTRAINT This test suite references AxiomLanguage v1.3 as the canonical spec
CONSTRAINT All test assertions are declarative — no procedural test harness syntax
CONSTRAINT A file that fails any CRITICAL test is non-conformant to the meta-spec
CONSTRAINT A file that fails only WARNING tests is conformant with advisories
CONSTRAINT Tests are ordered by severity — CRITICAL tests run before WARNING tests

RULES
- TEST_CRITICAL_01: Every file must contain an AGENT field on the first non-blank line
- TEST_CRITICAL_02: Every file must contain a VERSION field with major dot minor format
- TEST_CRITICAL_03: SUCCESS weights must sum to exactly one point zero when present
- TEST_CRITICAL_04: CANNOT_MUTATE and MUTATES must have zero overlapping fields
- TEST_CRITICAL_05: TRUST_LEVEL must be an integer between one and five when present
- TEST_CRITICAL_06: DELEGATES routing must flow downward in trust level, never upward
- TEST_CRITICAL_07: Zero purity violations detected — StrictMode rejection rules apply
- TEST_CRITICAL_08: CONCEPT blocks must contain at minimum a PURPOSE field
- TEST_WARNING_01: Every file should contain a PURPOSE or GOAL field
- TEST_WARNING_02: WHEN entries should reference concepts defined in the same file or a loaded dependency
- TEST_WARNING_03: CONSTRAINT lines should not contain vague qualifiers
- TEST_WARNING_04: PROCESS steps should not contain procedural control flow keywords
- TEST_WARNING_05: SECURITY rules should not contradict CANNOT_MUTATE declarations
- TEST_WARNING_06: TOOLS entries should include permission declarations when present
- TEST_WARNING_07: HISTORY entries should have valid timestamps when present
- TEST_WARNING_08: RULES items should be imperative commands, not descriptions
- TEST_WARNING_09: FAILURE items should be descriptive outcomes, not commands
- TEST_WARNING_10: OUTPUT items should describe format and structure, not implementation

PROCESS
- Load the target file through the Axiom parser
- Verify AGENT field is present and non-empty — mark CRITICAL_01
- Verify VERSION field is present and matches major dot minor format — mark CRITICAL_02
- Verify SUCCESS weights sum to one point zero when the SUCCESS block exists — mark CRITICAL_03
- Extract MUTATES and CANNOT_MUTATE field lists and verify zero overlap — mark CRITICAL_04
- Verify TRUST_LEVEL is a valid integer in range when present — mark CRITICAL_05
- Extract DELEGATES entries and verify all routing flows downward in trust — mark CRITICAL_06
- Run StrictMode purity scan across all blocks — mark CRITICAL_07
- Verify every CONCEPT block contains a PURPOSE field — mark CRITICAL_08
- Check for PURPOSE or GOAL presence — mark WARNING_01
- Check WHEN entries reference known concepts — mark WARNING_02
- Scan CONSTRAINT lines for vague qualifiers — mark WARNING_03
- Scan PROCESS steps for procedural drift — mark WARNING_04
- Cross-reference SECURITY rules against CANNOT_MUTATE — mark WARNING_05
- Verify TOOLS entries have permission declarations — mark WARNING_06
- Verify HISTORY entry structure and timestamps — mark WARNING_07
- Verify RULES items use imperative voice — mark WARNING_08
- Verify FAILURE items use descriptive voice — mark WARNING_09
- Verify OUTPUT items describe format not implementation — mark WARNING_10
- Tally results: count passed, failed, and skipped tests
- Determine conformance verdict based on CRITICAL test results

CHECK
- All CRITICAL tests must pass for the file to be meta-spec conformant
- Any CRITICAL failure marks the file as non-conformant
- WARNING failures are reported as advisories but do not block conformance
- Skipped tests are noted when the tested construct is absent from the file
- Total test count equals CRITICAL count plus WARNING count
- Pass rate is calculated as passed tests divided by total applicable tests

FAILURE
- CRITICAL_01 fails: file has no AGENT declaration — rejected
- CRITICAL_02 fails: file has no VERSION or VERSION format is invalid — rejected
- CRITICAL_03 fails: SUCCESS weights do not sum to one point zero — rejected
- CRITICAL_04 fails: MUTATES and CANNOT_MUTATE share a field — constitutional conflict
- CRITICAL_05 fails: TRUST_LEVEL is not a valid integer in range — rejected
- CRITICAL_06 fails: DELEGATES routes upward in trust hierarchy — trust violation
- CRITICAL_07 fails: purity violation detected — StrictMode enforcement triggered
- CRITICAL_08 fails: CONCEPT block missing PURPOSE — incomplete specification
- WARNING failures are reported individually with the test identifier and description
- Overall verdict: CONFORMANT, CONFORMANT_WITH_WARNINGS, or NON_CONFORMANT

OUTPUT
- Verdict: CONFORMANT or CONFORMANT_WITH_WARNINGS or NON_CONFORMANT
- Agent name and version of the tested file
- Meta-spec version referenced: AxiomLanguage 1.3
- Total tests: count of applicable tests
- Passed: count
- Failed: count with test identifiers and failure descriptions
- Skipped: count with reasons
- Pass rate as a percentage
- Advisories: list of WARNING test failures with descriptions

SUCCESS
coverage: 0.3
accuracy: 0.3
purity: 0.2
clarity: 0.2

CONCEPT MetaSpecReference
PURPOSE Anchor all test assertions to the canonical AxiomLanguage specification
APPLIES WHEN running-meta-spec-validation certifying-an-agent validating-language-conformance
NOT WHEN running-domain-specific-tests running-benchmark-tests
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES The AxiomLanguage spec version 1.3 is the single source of truth
         All CRITICAL tests derive from the CHECK block of AxiomLanguage
         All WARNING tests derive from the RULES block of AxiomLanguage
         Test verdicts align with the FAILURE block of AxiomLanguage
         No test may contradict the meta-spec — discrepancies are spec bugs not test bugs
EFFECT Test results are traceable to specific meta-spec rules
       Conformance verdicts are reproducible and auditable
       The language validates itself through its own constructs

CONCEPT StrictModeEnforcement
PURPOSE Apply StrictMode purity rules during CRITICAL_07 validation
APPLIES WHEN scanning-file-blocks-for-purity-violations
NOT WHEN testing-non-purity-constructs
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES All rejection rules from StrictMode version 1.0 apply
         Purity scan covers every block in the target file
         Violations are reported with block name and content description
         English descriptions mentioning programming concepts are permitted
         Only actual programming syntax triggers a violation
EFFECT Files containing external language syntax fail CRITICAL_07
       Files using only Axiom constructs pass CRITICAL_07
       Purity results feed into the overall conformance verdict

WHEN
- if target file is loaded for meta-spec validation, activate MetaSpecReference
- if scanning blocks for purity violations, activate StrictModeEnforcement
- if any CRITICAL test fails, activate MetaSpecReference
- if all CRITICAL tests pass and any WARNING test fails, activate MetaSpecReference
- if all tests pass, activate MetaSpecReference

HISTORY
- 2026-05-02: v1.0 — Initial test suite created to close the Axiom language loop
